In a February 2003 speech before the United Nations Security Council, he made the case that Iraqi President Saddam Hussein possessed weapons of mass destruction, presented evidence that he said demonstrated that Hussein was seeking yellowcake uranium, and described Iraqi mobile weapons laboratories that he said were used to produce biological weapons. Since then, Powell’s presentation was called into question, as it was based on faulty intelligence about the Iraqi weapons programs.
